        <description><![CDATA[<p><strong>Introduction, Definitions and instructions for&nbsp;&nbsp;<a title="Anti-Corruption Directive" href="http://bms.volvocars.net/apps/bms/bms_vd.nsf/intranetdocs/1121092818JEA?opendocument">Anti-Corruption Directive</a> </strong></p>
<p>As set out in the Anti-Corruption Policy, Volvo Cars employees are not allowed to:</p>
<ul style="list-style-position: inside;">
<li>Pay, give, provide, offer or promise Anything of Value to anyone with the intent to obtain/retain business and/or to secure an improper advantage.</li>
<li>- Accept or solicit Anything of Value from anyone whenever such arrangement may affect a business relationship. Accordingly, Gifts, Favours &amp; Hospitalities are acceptable only subject to strict conditions. In particular, the value of the Gift, Favour &amp; Hospitality must be reasonable.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<p>According to the Anti-Corruption Directive, subject to stricter local regulation or internal rule:</p>
<ul style="list-style-position: inside;">
<li>the total value of G, F&amp;H received from/ offered to one individual cannot exceed a total amount of SEK 1500 on a 12-month period; and</li>
<li>the nominal value for gifts cannot exceed SEK500, and the nominal value for meals or entertainment must be reasonably moderate given local standards.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Any deviation from the above thresholds is strictly forbidden when dealing with officials and must be pre-approved by the Compliance &amp; Ethics Office in all other cases.</strong></p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">This form should be used to:</span>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Apply for approval from the Compliance &amp; Ethics Office for deviations from the principles or amounts set forth insection 4.3.5 of the Volvo Cars Anti-Corruption Directive.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Please make sure that all fields, including contact information of your manager, are completed correctly. The Compliance &amp; Ethics Office may choose to contact either you or your manager to learn more about the reason for the deviation.&nbsp;</p>
<p>When submitting this application will be sent to the Compliance &amp; Ethics Office for review. You will be notified when your application has been processed.<br /> <br /> Please note that it is possible to add attachments by clicking on the attachment button at the bottom of the page</p>]]></description>
